---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="ICF Construction Ontario | ICF Homes & Basements" description="ICF construction cuts heating bills 50-70% and lasts 100+ years. Ontario ICF builder with 9 years experience. Get real costs, honest trade-offs, and a free quote.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section data-hero="dark" class="relative min-h-[70vh] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="/images/projects/image00004.jpeg"
        alt="ICF home under construction in Ontario"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-black/70 via-black/50 to-black/80"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 text-center text-white pt-24">
      <p class="section-label text-white/80 mb-4">Build Stronger. Save More.</p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-display font-medium mb-6">
        ICF <span class="italic">Construction</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-white/80 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        Walls that cut your heating bill in half and outlast your grandchildren. We've been building ICF homes across Ontario for 9 years.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">
          <span>Get ICF Quote</span>
        </a>
        <a href="tel:9057161939" class="btn-secondary border-white text-white hover:bg-white hover:text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">
          Call (905) 716-1939
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What is ICF - Featured Snippet Target -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-cream)]">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">The Basics</p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
        What is <span class="italic">ICF?</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="divider mb-10"></div>

      <!-- Featured Snippet Box -->
      <div class="bg-white p-8 md:p-10 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-timber)] mb-10">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-[var(--color-charcoal)] leading-relaxed">
          <strong>ICF (Insulated Concrete Forms)</strong> is a construction method where hollow foam blocks stack together like Lego, get filled with steel-reinforced concrete, and stay in place as permanent insulation. The result: walls 6-9 times stronger than wood frame with R-22 to R-26 built-in insulation and zero thermal bridging.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-pcm text-lg">
        <p class="mb-6">
          Here's the thing about ICF that most websites won't tell you: it's not new. The technology has been around since the 1960s. What's new is that Ontario builders are finally catching on. ICF home starts in Ontario are up 18% year-over-year, and the 2025 Ontario Building Code now explicitly recognizes ICF for two-storey dwellings.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          We started building with ICF back in 2016 because a client insisted on it for their Muskoka cottage. Skeptical at first, we watched that home sail through a brutal -35°C winter while the owners paid half what their neighbors did for heating. Now about a third of our projects use ICF in some form—either full walls or basement foundations.
        </p>
        <p>
          ICF isn't right for everyone. It costs more upfront. It requires crews who know what they're doing. And it's overkill for some projects. But for clients building a forever home in Ontario's climate? It's hard to argue against walls that pay for themselves in energy savings within 5-10 years.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How ICF Works -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">The Process</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          How We Build <span class="italic">ICF Walls</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div class="flex gap-6">
            <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-[var(--color-charcoal)] text-white flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 font-display text-xl">1</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-2">Stack the Forms</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)]">The foam blocks interlock and stack dry—no mortar, no mess. We cut openings for windows and doors as we go. A typical basement goes up in 2-3 days.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-6">
            <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-[var(--color-charcoal)] text-white flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 font-display text-xl">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-2">Install Rebar</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)]">Horizontal and vertical steel rebar goes inside the foam cavity. This creates a reinforced concrete core that can handle 250+ km/h winds and seismic events.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-6">
            <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-[var(--color-charcoal)] text-white flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 font-display text-xl">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-2">Brace and Pour</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)]">External bracing holds everything plumb and true. We pump concrete in 4-foot lifts, vibrating to remove air pockets. This is where experience matters—blowouts happen when crews rush.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-6">
            <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-[var(--color-charcoal)] text-white flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 font-display text-xl">4</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-2">Finish</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)]">The foam stays put—it's your insulation now. Drywall screws directly to plastic strips embedded in the foam. Outside gets whatever cladding you want: siding, stucco, stone.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="relative">
          <div class="img-zoom">
            <img
              src="/images/projects/image00008.jpeg"
              alt="ICF wall forms ready for concrete pour"
              class="w-full aspect-[4/3] object-cover"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="absolute -bottom-6 -right-6 bg-[var(--color-timber)] p-6 text-[var(--color-charcoal)]">
            <p class="text-3xl font-display mb-1">9+</p>
            <p class="text-sm font-medium">Years ICF<br />Experience</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ICF vs Wood Frame Comparison -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-charcoal)]">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label text-[var(--color-timber)] mb-4">Comparison</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-white mb-6">
          ICF vs <span class="italic">Wood Frame</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
        <p class="text-white/70 max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-6">
          The honest comparison. ICF wins on performance. Wood frame wins on upfront cost. Here's how they stack up.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white/5 border border-white/10 overflow-hidden">
        <table class="w-full">
          <thead class="bg-white/10">
            <tr>
              <th class="text-left p-5 font-display text-lg text-white">Metric</th>
              <th class="text-center p-5 font-display text-lg text-[var(--color-timber)]">ICF</th>
              <th class="text-center p-5 font-display text-lg text-white/60">Wood Frame</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-white/10">
            <tr>
              <td class="p-5 text-white">Wall R-Value</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">R-22 to R-26</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-white/60">R-13 to R-19*</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-5 text-white">Thermal Bridging</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">Zero</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-white/60">~25% of wall</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-5 text-white">Annual Energy Cost (Ontario avg)</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">$1,600-$2,800</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-white/60">$4,000+</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-5 text-white">Structural Strength</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">6-9x stronger</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-white/60">Baseline</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-5 text-white">Sound Rating (STC)</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">50-54</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-white/60">33-38</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-5 text-white">Fire Resistance</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">4+ hours</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-white/60">~1 hour</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-5 text-white">Expected Lifespan</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">100+ years</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-white/60">50-80 years</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-5 text-white">Upfront Cost Premium</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-white/60">5-15% higher</td>
              <td class="p-5 text-center text-[var(--color-timber)] font-medium">Lower</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-white/50 text-sm mt-4">*Nominal R-value. Effective R-value is lower due to thermal bridging through studs.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Benefits Section -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-cream)] grain-overlay">
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">Why ICF</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          What You Actually <span class="italic">Get</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">50-70% Lower Energy Bills</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Ontario's average home spends $4,000+/year on heating and cooling. ICF homes typically run $1,600-$2,800. That's $1,500-$2,500 back in your pocket every single year.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Built to Survive Anything</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Steel-reinforced concrete walls handle 250+ km/h winds. In tornado country, that matters. One of our Muskoka ICF cottages took a direct hit from a falling 80-foot pine. Dented the siding. Wall didn't care.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M3 12l2-2m0 0l7-7 7 7M5 10v10a1 1 0 001 1h3m10-11l2 2m-2-2v10a1 1 0 01-1 1h-3m-6 0a1 1 0 001-1v-4a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v4a1 1 0 001 1m-6 0h6"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Even Temperatures Everywhere</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">No cold spots by windows in January. No hot rooms in August. The concrete thermal mass absorbs temperature swings so your furnace and AC aren't constantly cycling.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M15.536 8.464a5 5 0 010 7.072m2.828-9.9a9 9 0 010 12.728M5.586 15H4a1 1 0 01-1-1v-4a1 1 0 011-1h1.586l4.707-4.707C10.923 3.663 12 4.109 12 5v14c0 .891-1.077 1.337-1.707.707L5.586 15z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Actually Quiet</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">STC rating of 50-54 vs 33-38 for wood frame. In real terms: you can't hear shouting through an ICF wall. Traffic noise, barking dogs, lawn equipment—all dramatically reduced.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">100+ Year Structure</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">Concrete doesn't rot, rust, warp, or get eaten by termites. The foam insulation is stable indefinitely. Your great-grandkids could inherit this house in solid structural condition.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card p-8 hover-lift">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 border border-[var(--color-timber)] flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-[var(--color-timber)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Higher Resale Value</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed">ICF homes sell for 5-15% more than comparable wood-frame homes. Buyers—especially informed ones—will pay a premium for lower energy costs and superior construction.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ICF Costs - Honest Numbers -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">Real Numbers</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          What ICF <span class="italic">Actually Costs</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center mb-8"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose-pcm max-w-none">
        <p class="text-lg mb-8">
          I'm going to give you real 2025 Ontario numbers. Most ICF websites are vague about costs because they want you to call for a quote. That's annoying. Here's what we're actually seeing:
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mt-10 mb-4">ICF Basement Only</h3>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Most common application. You get an ICF foundation with wood-frame above.
        </p>
        <ul class="mb-8">
          <li><strong>ICF basement walls:</strong> $38-$48 per sq ft of wall area</li>
          <li><strong>Typical 2,500 sq ft home:</strong> Add $15,000-$25,000 vs poured concrete with later framing and insulation</li>
          <li><strong>The catch:</strong> With ICF, the basement is already insulated and ready for drywall. No future finishing cost.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mt-10 mb-4">Full ICF Walls (Basement + Above Grade)</h3>
        <p class="mb-4">
          The whole envelope in ICF. Maximum energy efficiency.
        </p>
        <ul class="mb-8">
          <li><strong>Wall cost premium:</strong> 5-15% more than wood frame</li>
          <li><strong>On a $600,000 build:</strong> Add $30,000-$90,000</li>
          <li><strong>Total build cost in 2025:</strong> $320-$550/sq ft depending on finishes and location</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mt-10 mb-4">The Payback Math</h3>
        <div class="bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-8 mb-8">
          <p class="mb-4"><strong>Annual energy savings:</strong> $1,500-$2,500</p>
          <p class="mb-4"><strong>Premium paid for ICF:</strong> $15,000-$50,000 (depending on scope)</p>
          <p class="mb-4"><strong>Simple payback:</strong> 5-10 years</p>
          <p class="mb-0"><strong>30-year savings:</strong> $45,000-$75,000+ (not counting rising energy costs)</p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mt-10 mb-4">What Affects Your ICF Price</h3>
        <ul class="mb-8">
          <li><strong>Wall complexity:</strong> Straight walls are cheaper. Curves and angles add cost.</li>
          <li><strong>Concrete access:</strong> Easy pump truck access vs remote locations</li>
          <li><strong>ICF brand:</strong> Nudura and Logix cost more but install faster</li>
          <li><strong>Your contractor's experience:</strong> Inexperienced crews waste material and time</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-[var(--color-charcoal)] text-white p-8 mt-10">
          <p class="text-lg mb-4"><strong class="text-[var(--color-timber)]">Our honest recommendation:</strong></p>
          <p class="text-white/80">
            If you're building a home you'll keep 10+ years, ICF makes financial sense. The energy savings alone cover the premium. If you're building to flip in 5 years or less, stick with wood frame—the market doesn't yet pay the full ICF premium at resale in most Ontario markets.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ICF Applications -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-cream)]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="section-label mb-4">Applications</p>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-6">
          Where ICF <span class="italic">Makes Sense</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="divider divider-center"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="group">
          <div class="img-zoom mb-6">
            <img
              src="/images/projects/image00006.jpeg"
              alt="ICF basement under construction"
              class="w-full aspect-[4/3] object-cover"
            />
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">ICF Basements</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The sweet spot for most projects. ICF basement walls give you a warm, dry, mold-resistant foundation that's ready for finishing without additional framing or insulation. No more cold concrete walls in January.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-stone)] text-sm">
            <strong>Best for:</strong> Any new home where you want usable basement space
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="group">
          <div class="img-zoom mb-6">
            <img
              src="/images/projects/image00002.jpeg"
              alt="Custom ICF home interior"
              class="w-full aspect-[4/3] object-cover"
            />
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">Full ICF Homes</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Basement to roof in ICF. Maximum energy efficiency—these homes can hit Passive House performance levels without the engineering complexity. The ultimate forever home for clients prioritizing long-term value.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-stone)] text-sm">
            <strong>Best for:</strong> Custom builds where you're staying 15+ years
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="group">
          <div class="img-zoom mb-6">
            <img
              src="/images/projects/image00011.jpeg"
              alt="ICF cottage in Muskoka"
              class="w-full aspect-[4/3] object-cover"
            />
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-display text-[var(--color-charcoal)] mb-3">ICF Cottages</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-slate)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Muskoka and Kawartha winters hit -30°C. ICF cottages stay warm with minimal heating even when you're not there. Plus they're nearly immune to the tree-fall and storm damage that plagues cottage country.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-stone)] text-sm">
            <strong>Best for:</strong> Waterfront properties, remote locations, year-round use
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PCM's ICF Approach -->
  <section class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-[var(--color-charcoal)]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label text-[var(--color-timber)] mb-4">Why PCM</p>
          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display text-white mb-8">
            How We Build <span class="italic">ICF</span>
          </h2>
          <div class="w-16 h-px bg-[var(--color-timber)] mb-8"></div>

          <div class="space-y-6 text-white/80 leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              We do both ICF and wood framing in-house. Same crew, same project manager. That means we're not waiting on a specialized ICF subcontractor who's juggling five other jobs.
            </p>
            <p>
